-- Vestel Beyaz Hits 7-Month High on Parent Stake: Istanbul Mover
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-19T16:18:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/vestel-beyaz-hits-7-month-high-on-parent-stake-istanbul-mover.html
Vestel Beyaz Esya Sanayi & Ticaret
AS (VESBE) , a maker of home appliances, surged to the highest in more
than seven months in Istanbul after its parent said it bought
shares in the company.  Vestel Beyaz climbed 6.6 percent to 2.25 liras at the close
in Istanbul. The shares gained as much as 12 percent in intraday
trading.  Parent  Vestel Elektronik Sanayi & Ticaret AS (VESTL)  bought 110,761
shares in the company at 2.07 liras to 2.1 liras on March 16 and
104,206 shares at 2.02 liras to 2.05 liras on March 14, raising
its stake to 73 percent, according to filings with the exchange.  Vestel Elektronik advanced 5.6 percent to 2.27 liras, the
biggest gain in more than two months. Vestel was added to the
ISE National 100 index of shares, which tracks the countryâ€™s 100
biggest listed companies, the exchange said March 16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
